---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/sections/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | Wayon Automation">
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-4xl sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white p-8 md:p-16 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-indigo max-w-none text-gray-600 space-y-8">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              This Privacy Policy explains how Wayon Automation ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and protects information when users connect their Instagram, Facebook, or WhatsApp accounts to our platform. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your data.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>
              When you connect your Instagram, Facebook, or WhatsApp account, we may collect information necessary to provide our automation services, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
              <li>Name and Email address</li>
              <li>Social media account IDs (Instagram, Facebook)</li>
              <li>Profile information and public metadata</li>
              <li>Messages and comments (processed for automation features)</li>
              <li>Device and usage data for platform optimization</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. How We Use Information</h2>
            <p>
              We use the collected information for the following purposes:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
              <li>Provide and maintain our automation services</li>
              <li>Send automated responses to DMs, comments, and story mentions</li>
              <li>Manage product catalogs and lead generation flows</li>
              <li>Improve platform performance and user experience</li>
              <li>Provide customer support and maintain security</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Sharing of Information</h2>
            <p>
              We do not sell or rent user data. Information may be shared with trusted service providers (such as hosting providers) only to operate our services. We may disclose data if required by law or to protect our rights and user safety.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <p>
              Wayon Automation implements appropriate technical and organizational security measures, including encryption, secure servers, and strict access controls, to protect user data from unauthorized access or disclosure.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
              We retain user data only as long as necessary to provide our services or comply with legal obligations. If you disconnect your account, we will delete the associated automation data within 30 days.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. User Rights & Data Deletion</h2>
            <p>
              Users have the right to access, correct, or delete their personal data. You may:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
              <li>Request full deletion of your account and data</li>
              <li>Disconnect your social media accounts via our dashboard or platform settings</li>
              <li>Contact support for any privacy-related inquiries</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-6 p-6 bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl">
              <p class="font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-2">How to Request Data Removal:</p>
              <p class="text-indigo-800">
                You can request account and data deletion at any time by emailing us at <span class="font-bold">rameesvk551@gmail.com</span>. We will process your request and confirm deletion within 48 hours.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>
              Our services integrate with Meta platforms including Instagram, Facebook, and WhatsApp APIs. Your use of these platforms is also subject to Meta's own Privacy Policies and Terms of Service.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Users will be notified of any significant changes via email or platform notifications.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
              If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 font-semibold text-gray-900">
              Email: rameesvk551@gmail.com<br />
              Website: https://wayonautomation.com
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100 italic text-sm text-gray-400">
          Last Updated: March 14, 2026
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/" class="text-indigo-600 font-bold hover:text-indigo-700 transition-colors">
          ← Back to Landing Page
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
